== Documentation audiences == <!--T:46-->

<!--T:47-->
Primary users of the MediaWiki documentation and the most useful set of pages for each user-group are listed below.
</translate>

* '''Wiki users (end users of the MediaWiki software)''' <br /> {{ll|Help:Contents}} at {{ll|MediaWiki|mediawiki.org}} and [https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Help:Contents meta] are concise forms of end-user documentation.
* '''[[Special:MyLanguage/Sysadmin hub|System administrators]]''' <br /> Pages linked to {{ll|Category:MediaWiki for site admins}} and {{ll|Sysadmin hub}} contain sysadmin specific information. [[Manual:Contents]] serves as the reference guide.
* '''Wiki administrators''' <br /> [https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/MediaWiki_Administrator%27s_Handbook MediaWiki Administrator's Handbook] and {{ll|Manual:Administrators}} contain resources for administrators. {{ll|Manual:Contents}} serves as the reference guide.
* '''Developers'''
** '''[[Special:MyLanguage/Developers|Code developers]] and administrators''' <br /> {{ll|New Developers}}, {{ll|Manual:Contents}} and linked pages are a starting point for beginners. Experienced developers refer to {{ll|Developer hub}}.
** '''Add-ons developers''' <br /> References include {{ll|Developer hub}}, {{ll|Manual:Extensions}}, {{ll|Category:Extensions}}, {{ll|Gadget kitchen}}, {{ll|Manual:Bots}}, etc., besides the software installation guidelines.
** '''Designers''' <br /> Pages linked to {{ll|Design}}.
** '''Translators and technical writers''' <br /> {{ll|Translator hub}} and {{ll|Help:Contents}} for getting started followed by the project specific mediawiki pages.

For a more comprehensive exploration of the types of people who use Wikimedia technical documentation and their motivations, see [[Documentation/Audiences for Wikimedia technical documentation | Audiences for Wikimedia technical documentation]].

